President Obama will be hosting the leaders of Denmark, Finland, Iceland, Norway, and Sweden at the White House for a U.S.-Nordic Leaders Summit on May 13, 2016. The summit will focus on various issues such as countering terrorism and violent extremism, protecting the environment, coordinating on Arctic issues, promoting global health security, advancing sustainable development, enhancing nuclear security, providing humanitarian assistance, and addressing the migration and refugee crisis. The summit aims to deepen U.S.-Nordic cooperation and highlight America's commitment to European security, trans-Atlantic trade, and democratic values. The leaders will also be hosted for a State Dinner by President and Mrs. Obama.